Q1. How can you output “Physics” and “Wallah” in two different lines in C++?
Solution:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    cout<<"Physics"<<endl;
    cout<<"Wallah";
    return 0;
}

Q3. How much space does the following data types take?
. int
. bool
. float
Solution:
int - 4 bytes
bool - 1 byte
float - 4 byte

Q5. Write a program to find the circumference of a circle with radius 10 in C++.
Solution:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
    int r=10;
    float pi=3.14;
    float c=2*pi*r;
    cout<<c;
    return 0;
}


Q6. How many of these can be a variable name ?
. 01Pwskills
. _FLOAT
. int
. FLOAT
. You will succeed
Solution:
_FLOAT and FLOAT can be used as a variable name.
